<div class="flex gap-8">
  <%= render "docs/sidebar", current_page: "users" %>

  <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">👥 ZTLP Users</h1>
      <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500">ZTLP Users are network identities — separate from web login accounts.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">What is a ZTLP User?</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">
        A ZTLP User is a <strong class="text-gray-900">network identity</strong> — a person or service account that
        exists on the ZTLP network. This is <em>not</em> the same as a Bootstrap UI login account.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-3 rounded-md bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 p-3">
        <p class="text-xs text-amber-700">💡 Think of it like Active Directory: your Windows login is one thing, your AD identity (with group memberships and access rights) is another.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Identity Properties</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ztlp-600">Node ID</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">
            128-bit identifier (32 hex chars), auto-generated. The user's unique address on the ZTLP network.
            Not derived from cryptographic material — can persist even if keys are rotated.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-2 rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-2">
            <code class="text-xs font-mono text-ztlp-700">Example: a1b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6</code>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-ztlp-600">Ed25519 Key Pair</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">
            Generated automatically. Public key stored in DB and registered with ZTLP-NS.
            Used for Noise_XX authentication, signing NS records, and verifying identity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">User Roles</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <% [
          ["Admin", "bg-purple-100 text-purple-800", "Full control. Manage other users, create/delete groups, modify policies."],
          ["Operator", "bg-blue-100 text-blue-800", "Manage own devices and those they're responsible for. Limited admin access."],
          ["User", "bg-gray-100 text-gray-800", "Standard access. Connect via enrolled devices. Governed by group policies."]
        ].each do |label, color, desc| %>
          <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-4">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
              <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium <%= color %>"><%= label %></span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-500"><%= desc %></p>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">User Lifecycle</h2>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm mb-4">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-green-100 text-green-800">Active</span>
        <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800">Suspended</span>
        <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-red-100 text-red-800">Revoked</span>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-xs text-gray-500">
        <p><strong class="text-green-700">Active:</strong> Normal state. Can connect, authenticate, and access resources per group policies.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-amber-700">Suspended:</strong> Temporarily disabled. All devices blocked. Reversible — useful for investigations.</p>
        <p><strong class="text-red-700">Revoked:</strong> Permanently disabled. Keys considered compromised. Node ID cannot be reused.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-white border border-gray-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">User Relationships</h2>
      <div class="rounded-md bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 p-4">
        <pre class="text-xs font-mono text-ztlp-700">ZTLP User
  ├── Devices (1 to many)
  │   ├── Laptop  → own Node ID + keys
  │   ├── Phone   → own Node ID + keys
  │   └── Server  → own Node ID + keys
  │
  └── Groups (many to many)
      ├── "Engineering" → policy: access to dev servers
      └── "VPN Users"   → policy: access to gateway</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render "docs/prev_next", current_page: "users" %>
  </div>
</div>
